{"id":"binary-to-decimal","slug":"binary-to-decimal","name":"Binary to Decimal Converter","category":"converters","icon":"💻","description":"Convert binary numbers (base-2) to decimal (base-10). Enter any binary value (only 0s and 1s).","tags":["binary","decimal","number system","converter","base-2"],"fields":[{"id":"binaryLength","label":"Number of bits","type":"number","defaultValue":8,"constraint":{"min":1,"max":32,"step":1}},{"id":"bitValue","label":"Binary value (decimal input for bits × 2^n)","type":"number","defaultValue":10101010,"constraint":{"min":0,"step":1}},{"id":"decimal","label":"Decimal value","type":"computed","precision":0,"helpText":"Placeholder — use the explanation below"},{"id":"maxVal","label":"Max value for n bits","type":"computed","precision":0,"helpText":"2^n - 1"},{"id":"bitCount","label":"Bit count","type":"computed","precision":0}],"groups":[{"id":"inputs","label":"Binary (bits)","fields":["binaryLength"]},{"id":"outputs","label":"Information","fields":["maxVal","bitCount"]}],"formulas":{"decimal":"0","maxVal":"2^binaryLength - 1","bitCount":"binaryLength"},"explanation":"## Binary to Decimal Conversion\n\nEach bit represents a power of 2:\n\n| Bit | 7 | 6 | 5 | 4 | 3 | 2 | 1 | 0 |\n|-----|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 2^n | 128|64|32|16|8|4|2|1|\n\n**Example:** 1010 = 1×8 + 0×4 + 1×2 + 0×1 = **10**","examples":[{"label":"8-bit byte","inputs":{"binaryLength":8}},{"label":"4-bit nibble","inputs":{"binaryLength":4}}]}
